The static P3HT absorption spectra presented in Fig. 1 are measured by integrating the soft X-ray spectrum for 5 min with and without the sample in the beam. The sample absorbance (A) is then calculated from the sample transmission spectrum Is(E) and the background spectrum, I0(E) according to the Beer Lambert law, such that1AE=−log10IsEI0E.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
