				\begin{document}$$\triangle A\left(E\right)\,=\,-{{{{{{\rm{log }}}}}}}_{10}\left(\frac{{I}_{p}\left(E\right)}{{I}_{{up}}\left(E\right)}\right),$$\end{document}where Ip and Iup denote the sample transmission with and without the pump pulse. The signal is averaged over 15 repeated delay scans, and the error bars shown in Figs. 2,  3 and Supplementary Fig. 1 correspond to ±1 standard error and are estimated from the standard deviation of the repeated measurements. A two-dimensional Wiener filter is applied to the transient absorption spectrum to obtain the plots shown in Fig. 2. The temporal traces are obtained by integrating 1 eV regions centered at each differential absorption peak. The integrated yield of the negative differential feature, is subtracted from each yield to give the temporal traces.
